{{DISPLAYTITLE:Level 389: "The Black Goldmine"}}
{{Class 3e}}
'''Level 389''', also known as "'''The Black Goldmine'''<ref>Named after "black gold", a Victorian slang word meaning coal.</ref>," is the 390th level of the backrooms.

==Description==

{{Blurimage|caption=An image of level 389 showing soot accumulating and oil seeping through the walls|file=Blackgoldmine.jpeg}}{{Audio|file=389noise.mp3|volume=0.5}}
'''The Black Goldmine''', officially numbered as '''Level 389''', is a large network of tunnels and mines constructed within them, the bulk of which is made up of a series of circular corridors resembling abandoned station tunnels of a European metro system, covered in a thick layer of black dust.

This level is known to have one of, if not the largest supply of coal and oil deposits ever discovered throughout both the backrooms and the frontrooms. Based on the density of the coal and the sheer size of the level, it contains an estimated 3 trillion tons of coal within its boundaries, more than all the coal on planet [[The Frontrooms|Earth]]. This, along with easy access to [[The Metro]], has made the level one of the most tempting to colonise to major [[Groups|groups]] to supply fuel to bases where natural electricity isn't available.
{{Blurimage|caption=A cleaner area of the level used for human habitation|file=Cleancoalmine.jpeg|align=left}}

The abundance of coal dust and soot within the level can cause respiratory problems if one remains here long term. Pipes are commonly found within the tunnels, with a constant supply of oil flowing through them. While this may prove useful for an easy supply of oil should one need it, the pipes are notorious for leaking and drenching areas of the level with it. This provides a trip hazard and presents the risk of fire spreading throughout the level. As such, it is unwise to carry a naked flame while in '''Level 389'''.<ref>That being said, fires in this level cease to spread after a few metres. Without this property, nothing would prevent the entire level from burning down.</ref>
{{Blurimage|caption=An area that has been fully mined out and blocked off|file=wallarea.jpeg}}
Coal isn't deposited evenly throughout the level. In dustier sections of the level, it is common to break through a wall and find a straight wall of coal, whereas in cleaner areas, it may take longer to locate. Therefore, most groups tend to focus mining operations in the dirtier areas and use the clean tunnels for accommodation. The clean tunnels are also more likely to contain generators which further aid with colonisation. See the image above for an example of this.


Cave-ins are a common hazard on this level. Under normal physics, the tiled corridors would not be strong enough to stop the extremely dense coal from collapsing the tunnels, but here the tiles appear to have unusually strong resistance and rarely ever let coal through (with the exception of tiny dust particles). This effect is rendered useless for protection if tiles are removed for mining, so most groups block all areas actively being mined off with bricks to prevent civilian entry.



<Div style="background-color: black; margin:2em; padding:5px 10px; border:2px solid #FFFFFF; border-radius: 3px">
==Connection to [[The Metro]]==
With the level being set within station tunnels, it is unsurprising that '''level 389''' connects to a train themed level. Rather than having a singular station like in other levels, metro platforms in '''level 389''' are located all around the level in random locations. The easiest methods for finding the platforms are either finding the metal shell of a train tunnel while mining and following it until one finds a platform, or by simply following train sounds. These platform areas have become some of the most sought after by groups for the ease of trading the coal and oil found in the level with the rest of the backrooms.
</Div>
==The Oil Acropolis==
{{Blurimage|caption=An image of the Oil Acropolis and the Black River|file=Oilacropolis.jpeg}}
While the tunnels make up by far the largest section of the level, it also contains a large 200km² cityscape known as the Oil Acropolis, named due to the large river (referred to by inhabitants as the Black River) that flows through the centre of the city along with a network of estuaries, all of which contain an infinite supply of oil replacing the water one would expect. Just as the tunnels provide '''level 389''' with the largest known supply of coal, the infinitely resupplying black river provides the largest known source of oil. Access to the Acropolis is seemingly random. Very rarely, metal doors can be found inside the level which lead to random buildings inside the city. Finding a door like this while exploring alone is extremely unlikely; it is much easier to find a group that likely has them mapped and in use for transport routes.

When first discovered, the city was in an abandoned state similar to [[Level 11]], however as time has passed, groups that settled there have fully furnished the buildings and made the power stations and factories operational. Political tensions are very high within the level, but especially so in the Oil Acropolis due to limited space. All the land inside the Acropolis has been claimed by large groups seeking to claim as much oil and space for factories as possible. Carbon dioxide levels within the level have been rising at a rapid rate since industrialization, as has the average heat. Scientists have recently confirmed that '''level 389''' has a solar mass and atmosphere similar to Earth. If this continues, it is thought the heat will make the level uninhabitable by 2100.

Drone flights have shown the Oil Acropolis to be situated on a floating island. Strangely, jumping into the void below is not fatal. When one jumps, they are [[The Void|no-clipped]] into the tunnels, though likely not without injuries.

==Entities==
[[Entity 3|Smilers]] and [[Entity 124|clockroaches]] are occasionally found within the tunnels.

==Bases, Colonies and Outposts==
==Native Communities==
===State 51===
{{Blurimage|caption=The flag of State 51|file=State51.png}}
State 51 is the largest and most influential group on this level. The group was founded in 1968 by citizens of the United States of America who were intent on preserving American culture and ideologies in the backrooms. They initially resided in [[level 1]] but migrated to '''level 389''' shortly after its discovery, being the drawn by the promise of economic fortune and becoming the first group to colonise the Oil Acropolis, which they control a large portion of. Their current president, Morrison Shaw, aims to expand their influence and become a major group throughout the backrooms. However, this does not look likely as despite having a very strong military, their population is only around 7,000 and has no bases outside of this level.

<div class="titleblock"><span class="titlebox">File - Update.txt</span>
As of 2019, [[level 594]] has been rendered uninhabitable due to mental hazards. This has led to the surviving population being evacuated and bought to other groups as refugees. The most eager to accept them was State 51, which in a deal with the New American government agreed to grant all New American refugees citizenship and shelter in exchange for giving up their sovereignty, granting Morrison Shaw and the government of State 51 complete control over all recovered New American assets. This has been a major boost to their economy and population, which is now at around 19,000. While they currently remain almost exclusively within their home level, save for trade and scouting missions, it is rumoured that they intend to expand to other levels in the near future.
</div>

===Nowy Polski Syndykat (New Polish Syndicate)===
{{blurimage|caption=Flag of the Polish Syndicate, which was later repurposed as the flag of the New Polish Syndicate|file=polandsyndicate.png}}
The New Polish Syndicate is a large group of approximately 6,800 citizens, most of which were either born in Poland or have Polish descent. The group was founded in 1989, and is the second oldest and third largest colony in the level. The group was established by remnants of the Polish Syndicate, a once very large faction throughout the backrooms that collapsed under political turmoil. After this, many former Polish Syndicate citizens came together to form the New Polish Syndicate so as to prevent the collapse of their society and culture. While they are yet to reach the same heights as the Polish Syndicate that came before them, they have adopted the old group's flag and anthem to keep the impression of their former glory. To this day, the New Polish Syndicate remains by far the largest community of Poles in the backrooms.

The New Polish Syndicate has earned a reputation for astronomy. It was the group that discovered that '''level 389''' has its own sun and has invested billions of złoty into space exploration of the level. Despite the funding, expertise and 45 attempts at launching a rocket, all attempts at spatial exploration thus far have failed.

===Level 389 Mining Confederacy===
The Level 389 Mining Confederacy is a group of smaller civilisations and mining companies who came together to form a state of approximately 4,000 citizens. It initially began more as a business but over time has transitioned into a socialist state. The group has some of the best rights protection in the entire backrooms, offering basic housing and food free of charge. The majority of their territory is within the tunnels but they do control a small portion of the Oil Acropolis where their more expensive housing and businesses are located. 

The group has suffered controversies such as only holding elections once every 12 years, but is mostly praised as a nice place live by their citizens and a good alternative to [[Auto Nexus]] as a less militaristic socialist group if of course, one can cope with the poor air quality of their home level.
==Outsider Colonies & Outposts==
===[[Auto Nexus]] Black Sea===
A base controlled by Auto Nexus with the main goal of being the group's main mining and manufacturing hub. This is the largest base on the level controlled by an outside based group at around 6,000 members while controlling the second largest amount of territory (prompting frequent border disputes with the New Polish Syndicate). The base is highly militarised and usually hostile to members of other groups with the exception of the Level 389 Mining Confederacy.

Auto Nexus and the Confederacy have formed a close relationship with each other and frequently trade and share military intelligence. State 51 has accused the Confederacy of being a puppet state for Auto Nexus in an attempt to gain more territory and control civilians without the fear of them rising up against the Auto Nexus government. These claims have not been proven and the subject remains highly contentious among groups in this level.
===[[M.E.G.]]/[[Royal Exploration Unit|R.E.U.]] The Powerhouse===
The M.E.G. and the R.E.U. run a jointly owned base to give themselves true energy independence should a second [[Phenomenon 12|flicker]] occur and to avoid paying other groups for their fuel. They are close allies and are in defensive pacts with the New Polish Syndicate and State 51. 
===[[Backroom Colonists]] Base Fortune===
A small base situated mostly within the tunnels. Not very noteworthy other than it being the newest outpost in the level.
===[[Backrooms Investigation Foundation|B.I.F.]] Outpost Oil Rig===
A B.I.F. owned island in the centre of the Oil Acropolis used as an industrial base and an island prison, in addition to some territory within the tunnels. They are the most politically neutral group on the level and if relations between groups begins to get tense, they usually agree to use the island as a meeting point, with it being neutral ground.
==The Cold War of Level 389==
Unlike in [[The Frontrooms]], the backrooms having an infinite number of usually infinite levels means that territory disputes are few and far between. However, that is not the case with '''level 389''''s Oil Acropolis, which has limited space and infinite access to one of the most valuable resources. Groups that control more territory get more room for extraction machines and factories, making this land quite possibly the most valuable in the entire backrooms.

The tunnels are not spared from conflict either, as the scarcity of metro platforms made them very desirable locations to control. There have been several cases of bombs going off inside mines and inhabited tunnels, with the enclosed structure preventing escape.

As time has gone on and weaponry has become more advanced, the remaining groups have been left in a stalemate. From this, two major alliances have been formed, one between State 51, the New Polish Syndicate, M.E.G., R.E.U. and the backroom colonists and the other between Auto Nexus and the Level 389 Mining Confederacy, plus some other small loosely organised mining groups.
==History==
'''Level 389''' was discovered in 1971 after a member of State 51 discovered an entrance to it near their original base in [[Level 1]]. This prompted an expedition to the level to be undertaken in which the level's rich supply of coal and easy access to [[The Metro]] were discovered. The level was then slowly found by other groups which for the most part peacefully coexisted within the tunnels.

This continued until 1983 when the Oil Acropolis was discovered, leading to a scramble between the groups for territory and a period of fighting between factions known as the war of level 389. This war lasted for five years and saw the loss of thousands of lives in a period most residents look back on as pointless bloodshed for the benefit of their leaders. The conflict was ended after an agreement was suggested by the [[Backrooms Investigation Foundation|B.I.F.]], which would finalise the claims of all groups and officially declare them to be at peace.

The Polish Syndicate, which had suffered the most casualties, was hit the hardest by these allegations and collapsed under the pressure and backlash in 1989. While their presence in most levels of the backrooms quickly vanished, the local government in '''level 389''' were quick to react and send messages to the rest of the Polish Syndicate's former colonies inviting their inhabitants to '''level 389''', being careful to leave an image of continuing the Polish Syndicate's former glory while straying away from their militaristic past. This approach was very successful and on the 21st of May 1989, the New Polish Syndicate was officially established.

'''Level 389''' was among the few levels to actually benefit from [[Phenomenon 12|the flicker]]. Although they did have to deal with blackouts and an increase in entity presence within the tunnels, the coal and oil supplies made it easy for residents to provide their own electricity. During this time, generators and fuel from '''level 389''' became at their highest demand yet, and because of this, once the flicker ended groups based in the level as well as their citizens were left extremely rich.

The wealth from the flicker has come at a cost, however, that being that groups (particularly Auto Nexus and State 51) have been left with much higher military budgets. This has since provoked a chain reaction in which groups feel pressured to militarise to meet the capabilities of their rivals, resulting in the cold war we are left with to this day. Many citizens fear that war is going to break out once again, and that when it does, the chaos left behind will be impossible to rebuild from.

==Entrances and Exits==
===Entrances===
<div>
*Entering an extremely rare, rusted door with a picture of a pickaxe in [[Level 1]] will lead here.
*The tunnels in the bunker of [[Level 862]] may gradually transition to those of this level.
*Exiting a train on [[The Metro]] when it arrives at this level.
*Entering a metro station in [[Level 9]] leads here.
*Walking towards modern looking buildings in [[Level 503]] leads to the Oil Acropolis.
===Exits===
*Entrances from [[Level 1]], [[Level 862]] and [[The Metro]] also work in reverse.
*Entering a tunnel decorated with neon lights will lead to [[Level 154]].
*Being crushed in a cave-in can rarely [[The Void|no-clip]] one to [[Level 8]].
*Entering a café in the Oil Acropolis sometimes leads to [[Level 167]]. Cafés with this property will usually be labelled by whichever group's territory the café lies within.
